25/10/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliament and the OSCE Presence in Albania held a joint conference Wednesday (October 24th) aimed at launching a project to strengthen parliament's oversight role in the country's EU integration process.
The acting head of the Presence, Alex Finnen, was quoted as saying that the OSCE will help parliament's European Integration Committee do its job.
At the conference, the head of the European Commission Delegation in Albania, Helmuth Lohan, urged the various political parties to co-operate on important reforms in the judiciary and electoral systems, which are crucial to Euro-Atlantic integration.
(Panorama, Rilindja Demokratike, Shekulli, Koha Jone, Shqip - 25/10/07;
RTK - 24/10/07)
